      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I was just having a bit of fun with the goblin analogy. Anyway, back to the airport logistics.\n\nAt Heathrow, the most common way to travel between T3 and T5 is by the Tube (London's metro system) or the Heathrow Express. The Tube is a bit more complex, as you'll need to take the Piccadilly line from T3 to Heathrow Central, then transfer to the Tube to connect to the Piccadilly line again, which will take you to T5. It's a bit of a journey, and you'll need to factor in time for transfers and potential delays.\n\nThe Heathrow Express, on the other hand, is a more direct option. It's a dedicated train line that runs between Heathrow Terminal 2/3 and Terminal 5, with a journey time of around 15 minutes. It's a convenient option, but be aware that it's a single train per hour, so you'll need to check the schedule to make sure it aligns with your travel plans.\n\nJust look for the signs and announcements at T3 to get to the Heathrow Express or the Tube, and you should be able to navigate the transfer quickly and efficiently.",
